greeting: Greetings from The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences! http://oeis.org/

results.name: Square array A(n,k), n>=0, k>=0, read by antidiagonals, where column k is the expansion of Product_{j>=1} (1 - j^k*x^j).
formula: A(0,k) = 1 and A(n,k) = -(1/n) * Sum_{j=1..n} (Sum_{d|j} d^(1+k*j/d)) * A(n-j,k) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Nov 02 2017
results.author: _Seiichi Manyama_, Sep 10 2017
